Enable Service
1) check service status
    service sshd status

2) start service
    service sshd start

3) stop service
    service sshd stop

Enable Service Globally
1) check service
    chkconfig --list | grep -i servicename

2) enable service on default runlevels
    chkconfig sshd on

chkconfig --help

RunLevels:
  0 - Shut Down
  1 - Single User Mode (no networking)
  2 - Multi User w/no NFS (no networking)
  3 - Multi User Mode (CLI)
  4 - not used/research
  5 - X11 GUI
  6 - reboot
